sentences: Lars Salem Al Fakir (born 27 October 1981) is a Swedish musician, singer, songwriter and record producer.
In the autumn of 2006, Al Fakir released his first EP Dream Girl.

Beginning to collaborate with Avicii on "Silhouettes" in 2012.
Among the first co-writes with Vincent Pontare are Avicii's 2013 Billboard Hot 100 single "Hey Brother" and "Younger" by Seinabo Sey.
At the 2014 Swedish Grammy Awards, Al Fakir, Vincent Pontare and Magnus Lidehäll were awarded Composer of the Year after writing for Veronica Maggio's album Handen

Hey and Avicii's "The Days" and "Divine Sorrow" (with Wyclef Jean).
Al Fakir followed up with another successful year in 2015 co-writing most songs on Seinabo Sey's highly acclaimed debut album Pretend and songs for Madonna's Rebel Heart album.
